President Obama convened a National Security Council meeting to discuss the intensification of the campaign to degrade and destroy ISIL. The President was briefed on efforts to accelerate and integrate the military campaign and diplomatic efforts, including countering ISIL's goal of expansion beyond Iraq and Syria. The President emphasized that the United States will continue to counter ISIL terrorist plotters in any country necessary and directed his national security team to strengthen governance and support counterterrorism efforts in countries where ISIL has sought to establish a presence. The United States is committed to leading the shared efforts of the Global Coalition to Counter ISIL.